## 1. Executive Summary & Codebase Analysis

### What You Have

Your existing codebase is a **monolithic Python/Tkinter desktop application** that performs:

| Module | Lines | Key Algorithms |
|---|---|---|
| **MaxRects Bin-Packing** ([MaxRectsPacker](file:///home/victor/Documents/Work/SuperShaker/SuperShaker_v5.4.2.py#14-93)) | ~93 | Best Short Side Fit (BSSF) + center-biased packing for small parts |
| **Chip-Load Calculator** ([calc_t6_params](file:///home/victor/Documents/Work/SuperShaker/SuperShaker_v5.4.2.py#229-345)) | ~115 | Feed/speed calc for PCD/TCT tools on MDF/HDF with DOC correction |
| **G-code Generator** ([generate_gcode](file:///home/victor/Documents/Work/SuperShaker/SuperShaker_v5.4.2.py#1643-2434)) | ~800 | 4-op pipeline: pocket → corner-rest → miter/chamfer → contour cutout |
| **Nesting Engine** ([do_nesting](file:///home/victor/Documents/Work/SuperShaker/SuperShaker_v5.4.2.py#1151-1239)) | ~90 | Multi-strategy sort with rotation, 2-phase large/small packing |
| **PDF Export** (labels + cutting map) | ~280 | ReportLab-based per-part labels with minimap + B&W operator sheets |
| **3D Visualizer** (separate file) | 181 | Plotly Scatter3D with tool-separated rapid/cut paths |

**Dependencies:** `tkinter`, `pandas`, `reportlab`, `plotly`, [re](file:///home/victor/Documents/Work/SuperShaker/SuperShaker_v5.4.2.py#148-151), `json`, `math` — **100% pure Python, no native C/C++ bindings**.

### Key Architectural Insight

Your core is **CPU-bound pure Python** — no GPU, no native libraries, no FFI. This is both an advantage (easy to port) and a challenge (performance at scale). The recommendation below is calibrated to this reality.

