## 5. Backend Architecture & Data Management

### 5.1 Architecture: Modular Monolith → Microservices

> [!TIP]
> **Start with a Modular Monolith**, not microservices. At < 1,000 users, the operational overhead of K8s + service mesh + distributed tracing will slow you down. Extract services only when you have a scaling bottleneck.

**Phase 1–2 (PoC → MVP): Modular Monolith**

```
supershaker-api/                    # Single FastAPI application
├── app/
│   ├── main.py                     # FastAPI app + CORS + middleware
│   ├── auth/                       # Supabase JWT verification
│   ├── projects/                   # CRUD for projects, parts, sheets
│   ├── nesting/                    # Endpoint: POST /nest → calls core lib
│   ├── gcode/                      # Endpoint: POST /generate → queues job
│   ├── pdf/                        # Endpoint: POST /export/labels, /export/map
│   ├── billing/                    # Stripe webhook handlers
│   ├── admin/                      # Admin dashboard APIs
│   └── shared/
│       ├── db.py                   # SQLAlchemy + async PostgreSQL
│       ├── storage.py              # S3/R2 file operations
│       └── queue.py                # Redis queue (ARQ or Celery)
├── supershaker_core/               # Extracted pure-Python engine
│   ├── nesting.py
│   ├── chipload.py
│   ├── gcode_generator.py
│   ├── pdf_export.py
│   └── models.py
└── workers/
    └── gcode_worker.py             # Async worker: picks jobs from queue
```

**Phase 3 (Scale): Extract heavy services**

```
Services to extract when bottlenecked:
  1. gcode-worker  → separate deployment, horizontally scaled
  2. pdf-worker    → separate deployment (ReportLab is CPU-heavy)
  3. nesting-api   → separate if nesting becomes a hot path
```

### 5.2 Technology Stack — Backend

| Component | Technology | Justification |
|---|---|---|
| **Language** | **Python 3.12+** | Your core is Python; zero rewrite needed; FastAPI is best-in-class |
| **Framework** | **FastAPI** | Async, auto-docs (OpenAPI), Pydantic validation, WebSocket support |
| **Task Queue** | **ARQ** (Redis-backed) | Lightweight, async-native, Python-first; simpler than Celery for < 50 workers |
| **Cache** | **Redis** | Session cache, rate limiting, queue backend, nesting result cache |
| **ASGI Server** | **Uvicorn** + Gunicorn | Production-grade; multi-worker process model |

