    end

    DEV --> LINT --> TEST --> BUILD_API --> SEC --> STAGE_DEPLOY --> STAGE_TEST --> PROD_DEPLOY
    DEV --> BUILD_FE --> STAGE_DEPLOY
```

**Pipeline stages:**

| Stage | Tools | What it does |
|---|---|---|
| **Lint** | `ruff` (Python), `eslint` + `tsc` (TypeScript) | Code quality gates |
| **Test** | `pytest` with coverage > 80% | Unit tests for core algorithms (nesting, G-code, chipload) |
| **Build** | Docker (multi-stage) | `python:3.12-slim` base; < 200MB image |
| **Security** | Trivy container scan | CVE scanning on every push |
| **Staging** | Auto-deploy on [main](file:///home/victor/Documents/Work/SuperShaker/G-code%20Visualizer/gcode_viewer_gui.py#146-178) merge | Full environment with test DB |
| **Production** | Manual approve → blue-green deploy | Zero-downtime via ECS rolling update |

### 7.3 Handling Heavy Computational Loads

```mermaid
graph TB
    API[FastAPI API] -->|"POST /generate"| Q[Redis Queue - ARQ]
    Q --> W1[Worker 1]
    Q --> W2[Worker 2]
    Q --> W3[Worker N...]

    W1 -->|".nc file"| S3[S3 Storage]
    W1 -->|"Job complete"| WS[WebSocket Notification]
    WS -->|"File ready!"| CLIENT[Browser]
    CLIENT -->|"GET signed URL"| S3

    subgraph "Auto-Scaling"
        ASG[ECS Auto Scaling]
        ASG -->|"Queue depth > 10"| W3
    end
    Q --> ASG
```

| Concern | Strategy |
|---|---|
| **Job queuing** | ARQ (async Redis queue): submit G-code gen as background job; return job ID immediately |
| **Progress tracking** | WebSocket connection: worker publishes progress (parsing→OP1→OP2→OP3→OP4→done) |
| **Auto-scaling** | ECS auto-scaling based on Redis queue depth; scale workers 1→10 during peak |
| **Timeouts** | 5-minute max per generation job; user notified on timeout |
| **Caching** | Hash(project_params) → if identical inputs, return cached S3 file |
| **GPU** (future) | Not needed now; your algorithms are CPU-bound. Only relevant if you add CAD rendering or AI-assisted nesting later |

---

## 8. Definitive Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version | Why |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Frontend** | React + TypeScript | 18+ | Complex state, huge ecosystem |
| **3D Engine** | Three.js | r160+ | WebGL toolpath rendering, LOD, chunking |
| **State** | Zustand | 4+ | Lightweight, no boilerplate |
| **Styling** | CSS Modules + Radix UI | — | CAM UIs are too custom for Tailwind |
| **Build** | Vite | 5+ | Fast dev, optimal bundles |
| **Backend** | FastAPI (Python) | 0.110+ | Async, auto-docs, Pydantic |
| **Task Queue** | ARQ | 0.26+ | Async Redis queue, lightweight |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL | 16 | JSONB for flexible configs |
| **Cache/Queue** | Redis | 7+ | Session, rate-limit, queue |
| **Object Storage** | S3 or Cloudflare R2 | — | G-code, PDFs, uploads |
| **Auth** | Supabase Auth | — | JWT, OAuth, RLS, free tier |
| **Payments** | Stripe | — | Subscriptions, webhooks |
| **CDN** | CloudFront or Cloudflare | — | SPA + asset delivery |
| **Containers** | Docker + ECS Fargate | — | No server management |
| **CI/CD** | GitHub Actions | — | Free for public, cheap for private |
| **Monitoring** | Sentry + Prometheus + Grafana | — | Errors, metrics, dashboards |

