## 9. Phased Implementation Roadmap

### Phase 1: Proof of Concept (6–8 weeks)

**Goal:** Validate that the core engine works in a web context end-to-end.

| Week | Deliverable | Details |
|---|---|---|
| 1–2 | **Core extraction** | Refactor [SuperShaker_v5.4.2.py](file:///home/victor/Documents/Work/SuperShaker/SuperShaker_v5.4.2.py) into `supershaker_core/` library; remove all Tkinter deps; add Pydantic models |
| 3 | **FastAPI wrapper** | Create `/nest`, `/generate`, `/chipload` endpoints; input = JSON, output = JSON or file |
| 4 | **Unit tests** | pytest suite for nesting, G-code gen, chipload calc; compare outputs to desktop app |
| 5–6 | **Basic React UI** | Part table (CRUD), sheet config form, "Generate" button, file download |
| 7 | **Three.js viewer** | Port [gcode_viewer_gui.py](file:///home/victor/Documents/Work/SuperShaker/G-code%20Visualizer/gcode_viewer_gui.py) to Three.js with Web Worker parsing |
| 8 | **Integration** | Connect frontend ↔ API; deploy to Railway/Fly.io; demo to stakeholders |

**PoC Success Criteria:**
- User can input parts, run nesting, generate G-code, and download `.nc` files via browser
- 3D viewer renders 100K-line G-code files at 60fps
- G-code output is **byte-identical** to desktop app for same inputs

### Phase 2: Minimum Viable Product (8–12 weeks)

**Goal:** A product real users can sign up for and pay for.

| Week | Deliverable | Details |
|---|---|---|
| 1–2 | **Auth** | Supabase Auth integration; login/signup, JWT middleware |
| 3–4 | **Database** | PostgreSQL schema; project CRUD; machine profiles; tool configs |
| 5–6 | **Billing** | Stripe integration; Free/Pro tiers; feature gating; checkout flow |
| 7–8 | **PDF export** | Labels + cutting map generation; S3 storage; download links |
| 9 | **Job queue** | ARQ workers for async G-code generation; WebSocket progress |
| 10 | **Excel import** | File upload + parsing via Pandas; maps to project parts |
| 11 | **Polishing** | Error handling, loading states, responsive design, onboarding flow |
| 12 | **Launch prep** | Staging env, monitoring (Sentry), docs, landing page |

**MVP Success Criteria:**
- 10 beta users can complete full workflow: import Excel → nest → generate → download
- Stripe billing works end-to-end with Free/Pro tiers
- 99.9% uptime over 2-week beta period

### Phase 3: Scale & Polish (12–16 weeks)

| Week | Deliverable | Details |
|---|---|---|
| 1–3 | **Enterprise features** | Team management (orgs), RBAC (`admin`/`member`/`viewer`), SSO (SAML) |
| 4–5 | **Performance** | 3D viewer LOD for 5M+ lines; nesting result caching; CDN optimization |
| 6–7 | **Advanced CAM** | Shaker Step full support; custom strategies; multi-sheet batch generation |
| 8–9 | **API for Enterprise** | REST API with API keys; rate limiting; OpenAPI docs for integrators |
| 10–11 | **Analytics** | Usage dashboards; per-user metrics; conversion funnels |
| 12–13 | **Collaboration** | Shared projects; comment threads on nesting layouts; version history |
| 14–16 | **Internationalization** | i18n (EN/RU/DE); localized units (mm/inches); currency support |

